    <pre>I think I see the problem. When this view gets called, this exception gets raised:

TemplateDoesNotExist: account/widget.html

Karen, did this get broken by the redesign do you think?

As a note, I wrote this unnecessarily long sample code to reproduce the problem:

from django.contrib.auth import login
from django.test.client import RequestFactory
from django.contrib.sessions.middleware import SessionMiddleware
from django.contrib.auth.middleware import AuthenticationMiddleware
from django.middleware.common import CommonMiddleware

def create_request(url, username):
    rf = RequestFactory()
    request = rf.get(url)
    for m in [CommonMiddleware, SessionMiddleware, AuthenticationMiddleware]:
        i = m()
        i.process_request(request)

    # Get a specific user and log that user in (or change the user's name, or
whatever)
    user = User.objects.get(username=username)
    user.backend = 'django.contrib.auth.backends.ModelBackend'
    login(request, user)

    # Call the view directly with the new request
    return request

import mysite.account.views
request = create_request('/account/settings/widget', 'paulproteus')
mysite.account.views.widget(request)</pre>
